-- Zorlu Enerji Falls in Istanbul After 2011 Loss Misses Estimate
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-04-13T07:02:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/zorlu-enerji-falls-in-istanbul-after-2011-loss-misses-estimate.html
Zorlu Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS (ZOREN) , a
Turkish utility, fell in Istanbul after full-year loss widened
to 407.4 million liras ($227 million), missing estimates.  Zorlu Enerji dropped 1.8 percent to 1.62 liras at 9:55 a.m.
The loss widened from 66.7 million liras in 2010, Zorlu Enerji
in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange  after the market
closed yesterday. The company was expected to report a loss of
196.3 million liras, according to the average of nine analyst
estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
